Network Engineer
This position reports to the Director of Information Systems.
Appointment:
Annually renewable 12-month appointment.
Responsibilities:The Network Engineer is responsible for deploying and maintaining the network specifications by conferring with the department head; plan, design, and maintain the college’s network infrastructure and enterprise network solutions; install, implement, administer, and troubleshoot the network systems and provide support to the college campus. Analyze workflow, access control, and establish security requirements and router administration, including interface configuration and routing protocols. Maintain network performance by monitoring and analyzing. Secure network by developing network access control, monitoring, documentation, and evaluation of new related technology. Major responsibilities include, but are not limited to the following: Provide support to campus community on all facets of network, telephone, and network security;
Assist information systems peers and end-users on any wired/wireless network security, data communication, and telephone related issues;
Serve as primary contact for any network, telephone, and network security issues;
Participate in group discussion, meetings with department head, peers, or with end-users relating to maintenance, improvement, and troubleshooting the network environment. Additionally, engaging with peer institutions and vendors on any issue or upcoming system upgrades;
Maintain Extreme routers, switches, Extreme A-20 NAC, Palo-Alto / Check Point / Cisco ASA 5520 firewalls, VPN, Extreme C25 Wireless Controllers, Extreme access points, Asterisk Open Source telephony switching (VoIP) and NEC 2400 PBX system, maintaining large class “C’ IP network;
Plan short-term and long-term planning to meet current and future network requirements;
Perform other similar duties as required.



Bachelor’s degree required, Information Systems or Computer Science master’s degree preferred; must have excellent written and oral communication skills; relational database experience preferred. Must have an appreciation for and an understanding of a two-year college mission; candidate should have demonstrated awareness of diversity issues in higher education and possess skills in cultural competency. • Understanding of and experience with VLANs, NAT, HSRP, IPSec VPN Tunnels, QoS, OSI layers, voice and data communication protocols. • Expertise in TCP/IP packet analysis, using Wireshark or raw packet captures using tcpdump. • Solid understanding of Windows, Linux, VMWare networking, and SAN protocols. • Exceptional analytical and problem-solving skills, with logical problem-solving from Layer 1 through Layer 7 of the OSI model. • Network System Design and Implementation: Designs and implements network systems. • Network Connectivity: Provides support for network connectivity or related network issues for the user community. • Network Installation: Plans and monitors the installation of network systems. 
Salary:Commensurate with academic preparation and experience; plus full benefits package.
Application:
Submit materials electronically to the Office for Human Resources, Rhodes State College. Applicants must include a letter of interest outlining background and qualifications, a resume and the names, email addresses and telephone numbers (work and home/cell) of at least five (5) professional references. References are contacted at the point when applicants advance through the interview process. Applicants who are invited to the interview process will be required to complete and submit a College employment application. 
Rhodes State College is an equal-opportunity, Title IX institution and pledges to recruit, select and promote diversity by providing equality of opportunity in higher education for all persons, including faculty and employees with respect to hiring, continuation, promotion, and applicants for admission, enrolled students and graduates without discrimination or segregation.

The College is interested in candidates who have the communication skills and cross-cultural abilities to maximize their effectiveness with diverse groups of colleagues, students, faculty, and community members. All employment decisions are made on a non-discriminatory basis. Rhodes State College prohibits discrimination and harassment based on sex, race, color, age, national origin, religion, disability, genetic information, marital status, sexual orientation, gender identity and gender expression, citizenship, pregnancy or maternity, protected veteran status, work-related injury or any other status protected by applicable national, federal, state or local law. This nondiscrimination policy covers admissions, employment, and access to and treatment in College programs, services, and activities. A pre-employment background screen is required for all employees and the College participates in the Federally-mandated E-Verify program.

The Director of Human Resources, located in Room 223 of the Public Service Building, telephone 419-995-8302, coordinates the college's compliance with titles VI and VII of the Civil Rights Act of 1964, Title IX of the Education Amendments of 1972, the Rehabilitation Act of 1973, the Americans with Disabilities Act and amendments, and the Age Discrimination in Employment Act.

When you’re the best, we’re the best. We instill an environment where employees feel engaged, satisfied and able to contribute their unique skills and talents. We provide extensive opportunities for personal and professional development, building both employee competence and organizational capability to fuel exceptional performance now and in the future.Job Description:Summary:This position is responsible for data acquisition through the design, maintenance, and implementation of scripts and automated processes meant to retrieve accurate and complete data from various healthcare IT systems.  The data is used to meet members’ needs for information and comparative data unique to metrics for clinical, operational, and financial performance. The position also performs advanced technical tasks to support team function as assigned by their supervisor. This position ensures high quality data flows into bench-marking tools and reports used to support their efforts to meet challenges and improve efficiency to remain competitive in their marketplace.Responsibilities:Ensure the successful completion of quality product and solution implementation utilizing strong technical and analytical skills;
Work directly with multiple customers through the successful implementation of Vizient product/service offerings and/or technologies
Lead conversations with customer business and technical representatives with regard to all data aspects of new facility implementations;
Understand and analyze facilities' inbound data files, including claim, payment, demographic, charges, charge description master, spend and other data.  Identify where facilities' data meets requirements and where and why it does not.  Work with facilities to help them provide data that conforms to requirements;
Work with facility project team and IT personnel to coordinate the receipt and import of historical and on-going daily data into the database;
Build configurations, business rules, and data mapping using internal Vizient tools
Document detailed data import scripting, business rule configuration, workflow, and production job control specifications;
Test data import and workflow after they are developed;
Be a point person for data acquisition updates
Assist engagement consultants with defining and gathering requirements for successful engagement completion or product implementation
Actively contribute to the design and implementations of internal process improvements.  This involves improvement of manual processes as well as identifying, developing, and implementation of tools that help automate processes
Qualifications:7+ years' total experience with 3+ years’ experience with healthcare technologies
Intermediate-level or above using SQL (T-SQL, PL/SQL, Other) for data querying, analysis, and script development, preferably with healthcare information
Experience working through data acquisition solutions with Healthcare IT Systems such as Epic, Cerner, Meditech, Allscripts, GE; and/or Materials Management Systems such as Lawson/Infor, Meditech, McKesson, PeopleSoft/Oracle
Strong data management skills and understanding of relational DB structures – ability to learn the structure of a relational DB and in turn leverage the data as a business tool
Fundamental awareness or coursework in software development – understand programming concepts, ability to understand the logic of a computer program; ability to develop software will provide ample opportunities in future
Proven customer service skills in communication, both written and verbal, to facilitate the exchange of information with members
Excellent time management and prioritization skills
Bachelor’s degree is required, preferably in business, healthcare administration or a related field. Master’s degree preferred.
